    ("Chemistry", "Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers", "Identify the major product when phenol is treated with Br2 in CS2 at 273 K.", "p-Bromophenol.", "MODERATE"),
    ("Chemistry", "Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers", "Among isomeric alcohols, why do tertiary alcohols have the lowest boiling points?", "Due to maximum branching, which decreases the surface area and weakens van der Waals forces.", "EASY"),
    ("Chemistry", "Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers", "What type of alcohol is formed when a Grignard reagent reacts with methanal (formaldehyde) followed by hydrolysis?", "A primary alcohol.", "EASY"),
