    ("Chemistry", "Alcohols, Phenols and Ethers", "Why must the Williamson ether synthesis for preparing tert-butyl methyl ether use sodium tert-butoxide and methyl bromide, and not the other way around?", "Because a tertiary alkyl halide (tert-butyl bromide) would undergo elimination with a strong base to form an alkene (isobutylene) instead of substitution.", "HARD"),
