    ("Chemistry", "Aldehydes, Ketones and Carboxylic Acids", "Why is the alpha-hydrogen of aldehydes and ketones highly acidic?", "Due to the strong electron-withdrawing effect of the carbonyl group and the resonance stabilization of the resulting conjugate base (enolate ion).", "HARD"),
    ("Chemistry", "Aldehydes, Ketones and Carboxylic Acids", "Which is more acidic: Fluoroacetic acid or Chloroacetic acid? Why?", "Fluoroacetic acid, because fluorine has a stronger -I (electron-withdrawing) effect than chlorine, which better stabilizes the carboxylate ion.", "HARD"),
