    ("Chemistry", "Aldehydes, Ketones and Carboxylic Acids", "Does formic acid (methanoic acid) give a positive Tollens' test? Why?", "Yes, because unlike other carboxylic acids, its structure contains an oxidizable aldehydic part (-CHO).", "HARD"),
    ("Chemistry", "Aldehydes, Ketones and Carboxylic Acids", "Write the specific reagents used to perform the iodoform test.", "Iodine and sodium hydroxide (I2 + NaOH) or Sodium hypoiodite (NaOI).", "EASY"),
