    ("Chemistry", "Aldehydes, Ketones and Carboxylic Acids", "What happens when calcium acetate is subjected to dry distillation?", "It decomposes to yield propanone (acetone) and calcium carbonate.", "MODERATE"),
    ("Chemistry", "Aldehydes, Ketones and Carboxylic Acids", "Why is propanal more reactive than propanone towards nucleophilic addition reactions?", "Propanal has less steric hindrance and only one electron-donating alkyl group (+I effect) compared to two in propanone, making the carbonyl carbon more electrophilic.", "MODERATE"),
